==Comparison with other democracy-measuring data sets== The DD dataset is limited to 199 countries after 1946, whereas Boix, Miller, & Rosato, 2013 proposed a data set from 1800 to 2007, covering 219 countries. The 2010 version of [[Polity data series]] covers 189 countries from 1800 to 2009.<ref name= "Boix, Miller, & Rosato, 2013"/>
Gugiu & Centellas developed the [[Democracy Cluster Classification]] Index that integrates five democracy indicators (including the DD dataset, Polity dataset, etc.), clustering 24 American and 39 European regimes over 30 years.<ref name= "GugiuCentellas 2013"/>
