{{Infobox Organization|name='''emerge85'''|formation=2016|type=Joint Research Initiative|location=Washington, D.C. and Abu Dhabi|leader_title=Co-Directors|leader_name=[[Afshin Molavi]] and [[Mishaal Al Gergawi]]|website=http://emerge85.io/}}

'''emerge85''', originally known as The Johns Hopkins SAIS-Delma Institute Partnership on Geo-Economic Multiplicity, is a research partnership between the [[Foreign Policy Institute]] at Johns Hopkins [[Paul H. Nitze School of Advanced International Studies]] (SAIS) and the UAE-based Delma Institute.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://thehill.com/opinion/international/352513-can-one-unremarkable-street-in-dubai-explain-our-changing-world|title=Can one unremarkable street in Dubai explain our changing world?|last=Molavi|first=Afshin|date=2017-09-26|website=The Hill|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://drafts.delma.io/en/the-delma-institute-is-shifting-its-focus|title=The Delma Institute Is Shifting Its Focus|website=drafts.delma.io|access-date=2017-10-25}}</ref> The partnership is co-located in [[Washington, D.C.]], and [[Abu Dhabi]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2017/10/26/china-is-eyeballing-a-major-strategic-investment-in-saudi-arabias-oil/|title=China Is Eyeballing a Major Strategic Investment in Saudi Arabia’s Oil|website=Foreign Policy|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref>

Its stated purpose is to explore change and the rising importance of [[emerging markets]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenational.ae/opinion/how-the-gcc-and-china-stand-to-benefit-from-a-deeper-belt-and-road-partnership-1.665346|title=How the GCC and China stand to benefit from a deeper 'Belt and Road' partnership|work=The National|access-date=2017-10-17|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2017/11/22/saudi-arabias-populist-king-in-waiting-215857|title=Saudi Arabia’s Populist King in Waiting|work=POLITICO Magazine|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref> with emphasis on stories that challenge the economic status quo and reshape the global landscape.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fpi.sais-jhu.edu/emerge85|title=emerge85 Lab Initiative|last=|first=|date=|website=Foreign Policy Institute|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-10-17}}</ref> Recurring themes include urbanization, increased connectivity, and the [[global middle class]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sais-jhu.edu/content/johns-hopkins-sais-expert-available-discuss-global-economy-and-emerging-markets|title=Johns Hopkins SAIS expert available to discuss the global economy and emerging markets {{!}} SAIS|website=www.sais-jhu.edu|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://dubaieye1038.com/podcast/emerge85-lab-06-09-2017/|title=Emerge85 Lab, 06.09.2017 - Dubai Eye|work=Dubai Eye|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-US}}</ref>

The partnership derives its named from the [[World population|85%]] of the world’s population living in Asia, Africa, and Latin America.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sais-jhu.edu/content/new-johns-hopkins-sais-partnership-delma-institute-explores-dynamic-trends-shaping-emerging|title=New Johns Hopkins SAIS partnership with The Delma Institute explores dynamic trends shaping the emerging world {{!}} SAIS|website=www.sais-jhu.edu|access-date=2017-10-25}}</ref>

== History ==

emerge85 was founded in April 2016 and launched to the public at an event hosted by [[Vali Nasr]], the dean of SAIS, on October 4, 2016.<ref>{{Citation|last=SAIS events|title=SAIS Delma FPI Launch|date=2016-10-05|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6nrfKzO0nVs|accessdate=2017-10-17}}</ref> A year later in October 2017, emerge85 was an official partner at the fourth ALN Annual International Conference in [[Dubai]], which explored economic opportunities between [[Africa]] and the [[Persian Gulf]] region.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.zawya.com/mena/en/story/Africas_technology_innovation_provides_Gulf_investors_with_great_promise_at_ALN_Investment_Conference_2017_-ZAWYA20171005111032/|title=Africa's technology innovation provides Gulf investors with great promise at ALN Investment Conference 2017|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-US}}</ref> It also partnered with The [[Milken Institute]] for its 2018 MENA Summit in Abu Dhabi in February 2018, where Al Gergawi moderated a panel discussion on [[food security]] in the Middle East, and spoke on another panel about China's [[One Belt One Road Initiative]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.milkeninstitute.org/events/conferences/summit/mena-summit/program-detail|title=MENA Summit 2018 - Program Detail|website=www.milkeninstitute.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-22}}</ref>

== Leadership ==
emerge85 is co-directed by [[Afshin Molavi]] and [[Mishaal Al Gergawi]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gulfnews.com/opinion/thinkers/initiatives-to-enhance-us-middle-east-understanding-more-critical-than-ever-1.1933795|title=Initiatives to enhance US-Middle East understanding more critical than ever|last=News|first=Kerry Boyd Anderson, Special to Gulf|date=2016-11-22|work=GulfNews|access-date=2017-10-25}}</ref> Molavi is an author and senior fellow at Johns Hopkins SAIS and the [[New America Foundation]].<ref name=":3">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/international/archive/2017/11/asia-middle-class-trump-economy-trade/545657/|title=The Road to Making America Great Again Runs Through Asia|last=Molavi|first=Afshin|work=The Atlantic|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-US}}</ref> Al Gergawi is the managing director of The Delma Institute, a risk advisory firm located in Abu Dhabi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gulfnews.com/opinion/thinkers/mishaal-al-gergawi|title=Gulf News Thinkers: Mishaal Al Gergawi|last=|first=|date=|website=Gulf News|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-19}}</ref> Both Molavi and Al Gergawi regularly comment on emerging market affairs, appearing in the US media for ''[[The Atlantic]]'', ''[[Foreign Policy]]'', ''[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]]'', ''[[Politico]]'', and others.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3" />

== Publications ==
The partnership regularly publishes original articles and podcasts on its website. In October 2017, emerge85 published two reports, the first discussing how to bridge the Persian Gulf and Africa, and the second, looking at the energy ramifications of China's One Belt One Road Initiative.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/politics-economics/381091-why-the-uae-is-leading-the-charge-into-africa|title=Why the UAE is leading the charge into Africa|work=ArabianBusiness.com|access-date=2017-10-17|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://omny.fm/shows/businessbreakfast/building-africa-gulf-partnership-with-emerge85-19|title=Building Africa-Gulf Partnership with emerge85, 19.10.2017 - Business Breakfast - Omny.fm|website=omny.fm|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref>

=== Podcast ===
emerge85's podcast, "The 85%", was launched on August 7, 2017. The fortnightly show is hosted by Afshin Molavi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/the-85/id1271275248?mt=2|title=The 85% by emerge85 on Apple Podcasts|website=Apple Podcasts|language=en|access-date=2017-10-17}}</ref>

